LAGOS  – Plateau United has qualified for the final of this year’s edition of the NPFL/LaLiga Under-15 Promises tournament sponsord by MTN Nigeria Limited. In the first semifinal match played on Tuesday at the Remo Stars stadium, Ikenne, Ogun State, Plateau United of Jos defeated Sunshine Stars of Akure 2-1 in a tension soaked encounter. Umar Bala and Sumfat Julius scored for Plateau United while Olaniyi Precious scored the only goal for Sunshine Stars. To reach the final, the underrated Plateau United team shocked all and sundry at the quarterfinal by taking highly rated and favorites, Enyimba International FC Under-15 team to the cleaners, whitewashing them 4-1. Sumfat Junior put Plateau United ahead in the 7th minute, while Chinemerem Eze equalized for Enyimba FC in the 24th minute. On resumption of the second half, Samuel Aputezie made it two for Plateau United in the 47th minute before Kelvin Adeyemo made it three in the 51st minute and five minutes later, Umar Bala’s scored the final goal in the 56th minute added the icing on the cake to finally drown the baby elephants and oust them from the tournament. Plateau United will now play the winner of the second semifinal between defending champions, Remo Stars of Ikenne and El Kanemi Warriors of Maiduguri in the final.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒